><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532594\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532594\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tzm1665702658496.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tzm1665702658496.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tzm1665702658496.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tzm1665702658496\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specifies the location to which Uniface compiles objects, and from which objects are read by the Uniface test environment.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__topic_d142790e1_d142791e1_d142792e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__p_d142793e1_d142794e1_d142795e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$RESOURCES_OUTPUT</span> { <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code> }\n               {<var class=\"keyword varname\">Path/</var>}<var class=\"keyword varname\">Directory</var></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__section_yyj_4wv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d440172e67\">Arguments</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__p_d142799e1_d142800e1_d142801e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Path/Directory</var>—directory path and name; if a path is omitted, the\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">Directory</var> is placed in the working directory.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__section_k2h_qwv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d440172e82\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__table_d17171e1_d17172e1_d17173e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.asn</span>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">none </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__section_fwb_twv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d440172e130\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__p_d142808e1_d142809e1_d142810e1\">If <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$RESOURCES_OUTPUT</span> is\n            specified , the compiled objects are written to the specified path as separate files in\n            the standardized directory structure. This is usually a directory, but it can also be an\n            archive file (<span class=\"ph filepath\">.uar</span>).</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__note_uww_5wv_jwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Specifying a UAR file can carry a performance\n            penalty. In an environment where multiple users write to a shared location, it can cause\n            locking problems. It is usually only useful when preparing an application for\n            deployment.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__section_ifn_xwv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d440172e148\">Redirecting files</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__p_d142814e1_d142815e1_d142816e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$RSO</span> path setting can be\n            used to redirect non-standard resource files listed in the [FILES] section. For\n            example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__pre_nsc_ywv_jwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">myfile.txt = $RSO:TXT/*.txt</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__p_d142817e1_d142818e1_d142819e1\">This assignment resolves the path of\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">myfile.txt</span> via the path specified by\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$RESOURCES_OUTPUT</span>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__section_ub5_fxv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d440172e173\">Example: Using $RESOURCES_OUTPUT</h2>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__pre_lqc_ywv_jwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; ide.asn\n[SETTINGS]\n$RESOURCES_OUTPUT = usys:project/RSO \n </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__p_d142823e1_d142824e1_d142825e1\">When preparing application files for deployment, it\n            can be useful to compile objects directly to a UAR file. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__pre_z4c_ywv_jwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; ide.asn\n[SETTINGS]\n$RESOURCES_OUTPUT = usys:project/myapp.uar \n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__section_rth_1xv_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d440172e188\">Example: Directing Output to a Remote UAR</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__p_d142829e1_d142830e1_d142831e1\">If you want to compile to a remote UAR, you need to\n            edit both the <span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.asn</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">userver.asn</span>. For\n            example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"tzm1665702658496__pre_d4c_ywv_jwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; ide.asn\n[PATHS]\n$TCP TCP:|remote_host|user|password\n[SETTINGS]\n$RESOURCES_OUTPUT = $TCP:myapp.uar \n \nuserver.asn[FILES]myapp.uar path/to/the/myapp.uar</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvd1665702658647.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Standardized Directory Structure</a><p>Runtime objects are always stored in a fixed directory structure, whether that is in a compilation output directory or a deployed Uniface archive file.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532594\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532594\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$RESOURCES_OUTPUT Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specifies the location to which Uniface compiles objects, and from which objects are read by the Uniface test environment. $RESOURCES_OUTPUT { = } { Path/ } Directory Arguments Path/Directory —directory path and name; if a path is omitted, the Directory is placed in the working directory. Defaults Assignment file: ide.asn Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: none Description If $RESOURCES_OUTPUT is specified , the compiled objects are written to the specified path as separate files in the standardized directory structure. This is usually a directory, but it can also be an archive file ( .uar ). Note: Specifying a UAR file can carry a performance penalty. In an environment where multiple users write to a shared location, it can cause locking problems. It is usually only useful when preparing an application for deployment. Redirecting files The $RSO path setting can be used to redirect non-standard resource files listed in the [FILES] section. For example: myfile.txt = $RSO:TXT/*.txt Copy This assignment resolves the path of myfile.txt via the path specified by $RESOURCES_OUTPUT . Example: Using $RESOURCES_OUTPUT ; ide.asn [SETTINGS] $RESOURCES_OUTPUT = usys:project/RSO Copy When preparing application files for deployment, it can be useful to compile objects directly to a UAR file. For example: ; ide.asn [SETTINGS] $RESOURCES_OUTPUT = usys:project/myapp.uar Copy Example: Directing Output to a Remote UAR If you want to compile to a remote UAR, you need to edit both the ide.asn and userver.asn . For example: ; ide.asn [PATHS] $TCP TCP:|remote_host|user|password [SETTINGS] $RESOURCES_OUTPUT = $TCP:myapp.uar userver.asn[FILES]myapp.uar path/to/the/myapp.uar Copy Related Links Standardized Directory Structure Runtime objects are always stored in a fixed directory structure, whether that is in a compilation output directory or a deployed Uniface archive file. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}